  "body": "**Do you want to request a *feature* or report a *bug*?**\r\n\r\nNot sure if it's intended behavior, but if it is, I'd like this feature.\r\n\r\n**What is the current behavior?**\r\n\r\ncomponentWillUnmount does not get called on a portal element which was mounted by unstable_renderSubtreeIntoContainer when unmountComponentAtNode is called.\r\n\r\n**If the current behavior is a bug, please provide the steps to reproduce and if possible a minimal demo of the problem via https://jsfiddle.net or similar (template: https://jsfiddle.net/84v837e9/).**\r\n\r\nPlease check the example at:\r\nhttps://codepen.io/woutervh/pen/JJqpLq?editors=1111\r\n\r\n**What is the expected behavior?**\r\n\r\nIn the example above, I'd expect componentWillUnmount to be called, and the interval timeout to be cleared.\r\n\r\n**Which versions of React, and which browser / OS are affected by this issue? Did this work in previous versions of React?**\r\n\r\nGoogle Chrome | 59.0.3071.115 (Official Build) (64-bit) (cohort: Stable)\r\nTried with React version 15.6.0\r\n\r\n",
